<br>
Item Haste<br>
Spell Haste<br>
<br>
Item haste refers to items such as the FBSS with a permanent haste effect.  The largest haste of this type (if many are worn) is what is used, the rest are ignored.<br>
<br>
Spell haste includes any haste's from any spells that are cast on you (including bard songs, which are spells with a different name and a low duration).  Like any other spells that have similar effects, most do not stack with each other, but there are exceptions.  I don't know of every haste spell there is, which stack, etc.  I can tell you that the monk epic effect is actually a bard song effect that they have to keep clicking to keep the effect, and up until recently it did not stack with chanter haste spells.<br>
<br>
<br>
For FT items, I believe that you can have 1 of each type of item, and they will stack (eg. a FT 1 and a FT2 will stack, but not 2 FT1's).  It's pretty hard to measure mana regen that accuratly, so I don't know if we'll ever have that good of an answer on this. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ujerrek.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jerrek</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/24/01 7:29:55 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: How many FT items can a wizard get?</span><hr size=1> I've posted this question to the Dev board on more than one occasion and I even sent Mr. Van Couvering an email.. is it any surprise that none have been replied to?<br>
